The area offers two picnic tables, two coal grills, electricity, and is located near restroom facilities and trailheads. It also features a large amphitheater that is a popular area for school groups, public events and presentations. The facility is available year-round. Map to Reservation Areas Fee Rates   Group Size Weekends/Holidays Weekdays/Senior Citizens Damage Deposit 1-50 $50.00 $25.00 $50.00   Carolino Canyon Reservation Area This 40-acre day use facility is nestled in the juniper-pinon forests of the East Mountains, 9 miles south of Tijeras on NM Highway 337. The area can accommodate up to 250 people and provides 2 separate picnic areas. Map to Reservation Areas Upper Picnic Area The upper picnic area has a rustic shelter with a fireplace, tree-shaded tables, grills, restrooms, electricity and water. The area provides universal access with a paved nature trail. Lower Picnic Area The lower picnic area is just right for company
